rComments: He's a decent lecturer, very fair marker. All of the tests were based entirely on lecture and I seriously regret buying the textbook. Frankly, it was cruel of him to assign a book we used for only a few weeks that costs $80+. Besides that, he explains things well and you'll like the class if you care about income inequality.
Extremely difficult course, boring lectures, and a crazy amount of readings. Not worth the effort
An amazing course, although very challenging and time consuming.

rComments: This class was okay but sometimes I found it dull. The TA and the professor have high standards so you have to work hard. I did find the instructions for the final paper to be convoluted. It would have been more interesting if we could focus on 1 specific area as opposed to ensuring that we demonstrate our understanding of all of the material.

The  lectures are well organized, comprehensive and interesting.  He engages the readings in his lectures, sums them up  and posts slides. He also really engages you with the topic through  discussion and videos. The tests and assignments are fair. Definitely would love to have him again. He needs to use the mic though.

This is one of the most challenging classes(in a good way) I've taken so far. Prof. Wodtke really gets you to think critically about the material and class theory.  His lectures are very clear, interesting and easy to follow. He provides lecture notes as well, which is helpful. I would definitely recommend him as a professor.
